I am exploring the most toxic place in Dark Souls 2
I'm amazed I'm not raging yet, lol

I still haven't gone through DS3 that I bought yet...
Just learned I can destroy the poison spitters
Trust me, you will learn toxic
And they name is blowdart snipers]
They're a nonrespawning enemy that are found only in Blighttown
Blighttown is the most toxic place in DS1, figuratively and metaphorically
The whole lore is that it's a town beneath anor londo, and it's where all the filth ends up
Urgh...kinda like the Undercity in Judge Dredd tehen.

All the citizens are diseased and filthy.  The environment is poisonous.  There are mosquitos that can poison you, big giants with huge clubs that can also poison you (if they don't smash your face in), and then the worst douches of all, the blowdarts...
Low light limited vision environment with enemies that can start sniping at you from out of sight
The worst part is that they inflict toxic, a far more deadly version of poison that lasts longer and deals far more damage per tick
As a noob,you'll probably be dying and / or dark signing / homeward boning back to bonfires a lot
Veteran players know to farm the plant things in the Darkmoon Garden (ideally with a covetous gold serpent ring) to gather purple moss and blooming purple moss
The blooming one cures poison AND toxic
So before you head down there, if it's your first time you want a healthy supply of them
Veteran players can either grab just a few, or none at all
Also a pro tip, get the Spider Shield
Still trying to swim through Subnautica
And Space Hulk Deathwing on No Mercy
It's the starting item for bandits iirc, and you can find one in the sewers just before Blighttown
It has a hidden effect where it can block poison attacks
If you try to block the giant's club or the sniper's blowdarts with any other shield, you'll start buildup of poison / toxic
